<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="part-v">part <strong><em>v</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /pɑːt/    美 /pɑːrt/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.<strong>[正式用语] (使) 分开；(使) 分离：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The long wall parts the city into two areas. 
长长的城墙将城市一分为二。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The wind parted the smoke just enough for him to catch sight of Sibson. 
风吹散了浓烟，刚好让他看见了希伯森。</p><footer>2012 四川</footer></div>

<h4 id="2">2.<strong>分手；告别：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We parted at the airport. 
我们在机场告别。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="part-with">part with</h3>
<p>1.<strong>(不情愿地) 放弃：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The novel is so attractive that I can’t stand parting with it. 
这部小说引人入胜，我简直爱不释手。</p></div></div>